Note:
MANIFEST - Native Runa Package Manifest (Tier 1)

The canonical Runa package manifest substrate replacing Cargo.toml,
package.json, pyproject.toml, go.mod, and Dockerfile-style manifests.
Implements parsing and serialization of the canonical runa-manifest
textual format (a runa-config Section block at root level).

A Manifest is a CV_MAP with the following top-level keys:
  package         : Section with name, version, description, authors,
                    license, repository, homepage
  dependencies    : Section keyed by name, value = version-spec string
                    OR a Section with version/registry/git/path keys
  dev_dependencies, build_dependencies, optional_dependencies :
                    same shape as dependencies
  features        : Section keyed by feature name; value = list of
                    dep-or-feature strings (optional features)
  targets         : Section with lib + bin + test + example subsections
  build_config    : Section with edition, opt_level, lto, codegen_units
  runtime         : Section with image, command, env, ports, volumes -
                    covers Docker manifest scope

The actual record layout is the same as config.runa's CV_MAP; this
module adds typed accessors and a validator. Existing rich code in
manifest/package_manifest.runa is the binary-record implementation; this
module wraps the textual interchange surface so callers can:

  manifest_parse(source)        -> CV_MAP
  manifest_serialize(manifest)  -> textual source
  manifest_validate(manifest)   -> List<ValidationIssue>
  manifest_resolve_dependencies(manifest, resolver_cb) -> resolved dict

The textual format uses the runa_config grammar; we add convenience
constants for the well-known section names so callers don't have to
re-spell them.

References:
  - Cargo manifest    https://doc.rust-lang.org/cargo/reference/manifest.html
  - npm package.json  https://docs.npmjs.com/cli/v10/configuring-npm/package-json
  - pyproject.toml    https://peps.python.org/pep-0621/
  - go.mod            https://go.dev/ref/mod#go-mod-file
  - Dockerfile        https://docs.docker.com/reference/dockerfile/
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_primitive.runa" as StringPrim
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dict
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/string_builder.runa" as SB
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/config/config.runa" as Cfg
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/config/runa_config.runa" as RC
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/intrinsics/builtins.runa" as Builtins

Note: ============================================================================
Note: PARSE
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Parse a manifest source text into a CV_MAP whose root contains the
package/dependencies/etc sections.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Delegate to runa_config_parse which yields the same shape.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on parse failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "manifest_parse" takes source as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc runa_config_parse from RC with source
End Process

@Reasoning
Serialize a manifest CV_MAP back to its textual source form.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Delegate to runa_config_serialize.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "manifest_serialize" takes manifest as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc runa_config_serialize from RC with manifest
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: ACCESSORS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Lookup a value at "package.<key>" in the manifest. Returns 0 if any
intermediate section is missing.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Use config_get on the root map after asserting it is CV_MAP.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|key|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on missing or wrong-kind input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "manifest_package_field" takes manifest as Integer, field as Integer returns Integer:
    If manifest is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If field is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let mk be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with manifest, 0
    If mk is not equal to 6:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let root_map be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with manifest, 8
    Let pkg_cv be proc get from Dict with root_map, "package"
    If pkg_cv is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let pk be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with pkg_cv, 0
    If pk is not equal to 6:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let pkg_map be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with pkg_cv, 8
    Return proc get from Dict with pkg_map, field
End Process

@Reasoning
Convenience: read manifest.package.name as a String.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
manifest_package_field("name"); verify CV_STRING.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on missing or wrong kind.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "manifest_name" takes manifest as Integer returns Integer:
    Let v be proc manifest_package_field with manifest, "name"
    If v is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let k be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with v, 0
    If k is not equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with v, 8
End Process

@Reasoning
Convenience: read manifest.package.version.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
manifest_package_field("version"); verify CV_STRING.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on missing or wrong kind.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "manifest_version" takes manifest as Integer returns Integer:
    Let v be proc manifest_package_field with manifest, "version"
    If v is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let k be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with v, 0
    If k is not equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with v, 8
End Process

@Reasoning
Return the dependencies sub-map (CV_MAP) or 0 if missing.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Direct root lookup.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on missing.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "manifest_dependencies" takes manifest as Integer returns Integer:
    If manifest is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let mk be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with manifest, 0
    If mk is not equal to 6:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let root_map be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with manifest, 8
    Let dep_cv be proc get from Dict with root_map, "dependencies"
    If dep_cv is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let dk be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with dep_cv, 0
    If dk is not equal to 6:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with dep_cv, 8
End Process

@Reasoning
Return the dev_dependencies sub-map (CV_MAP) or 0 if missing.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Direct root lookup.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on missing.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "manifest_dev_dependencies" takes manifest as Integer returns Integer:
    If manifest is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let mk be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with manifest, 0
    If mk is not equal to 6:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let root_map be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with manifest, 8
    Let dep_cv be proc get from Dict with root_map, "dev_dependencies"
    If dep_cv is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let dk be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with dep_cv, 0
    If dk is not equal to 6:
